        <briefdescription>
<para>Getter function to retrieve the reset reason. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to unsigned int variable to store content of register RESETREAS </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>reason_str</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Reset reason as string representation</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
Function retrieve the reset reason from register RESETREAS by calling function nrfx_reset_reason_get and store the value in variable reason and assign it to pointer mask. It count the number of reasons by calling function popcount and clear register RESETREAS by calling function nrfx_reset_reason_clear. According to the content of variable reason a string variable will be filled, in case of more than one reset reasons string will be expanded. Finally string will be assigned to pointer reason_str. Both parameter will be passed to caller of this function. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
